 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$[{C_1} \to {C_1} - 8{C_3}]$$<br><br>[$$\because$$ two columns of determinant are same, then value of determinant is zero.]<br><br>2. $$\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; a &amp; {b + c}  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; {c + a}  \cr 
   1 &amp; c &amp; {a + b}  \cr 

 } } \right| = \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; a &amp; {a + b + c}  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; {a + b + c}  \cr 
   1 &amp; c &amp; {a + b + c}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$[{C_3} \to {C_2} + {C_3}]$$<br><br>$$ = (a + b + c)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; a &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; c &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>[$$\because$$ two columns of determinant are same, then value of determinant is zero]<br><br>3. $$\left| {\matrix{
   0 &amp; c &amp; b  \cr 
   { - c} &amp; 0 &amp; a  \cr 
   { - b} &amp; { - a} &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 0(0 + {a^2}) - c(0 + ab) + b(ac - 0)$$ [expanding with respect to R<sub>1</sub>]<br><br>$$ = 0 - c(ab) + b(ac) =  - abc + abc = 0$$<br><br>Hence, 1, 2, and 3 determinants have value 'zero'.

$$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $${A^2} = A.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right].\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {1 + 1} &amp; { - 1 - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1 - 1} &amp; {1 + 1}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>and $${A^3} = {A^2}.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right].\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {2 + 2} &amp; { - 2 - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2 - 2} &amp; {2 + 2}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Now, <br><br>$${A^3} - 2{A^2} = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right] - 2\left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right] + \left[ {\matrix{
   { - 4} &amp; 4  \cr 
   4 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {4 - 4} &amp; { - 4 + 4}  \cr 
   { - 4 + 4} &amp; {4 - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>= a null matrix

The system of equations<br><br>$$2x + y - 3z = 5$$<br><br>$$3x - 2y + 2z = 5$$<br><br>and $$5x - 3y - z = 16$$<br><br>$$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 1 &amp; { - 3}  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 
   5 &amp; { - 3} &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\left| A \right| = 2[ - 2( - 1) - 2( - 3)] - 1[3( - 1) - 2(5)] + ( - 3)[3( - 3) - ( - 2)(5)]$$<br><br>$$ = 2(8) - 1( - 13) - 3(1)$$<br><br>$$ = 16 + 13 - 3 = 26 \ne 0$$<br><br>So, system is consistent with unique solution.

Since, the vectors are coplanar.<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\left| {\matrix{
   \alpha  &amp; \alpha  &amp; \gamma   \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   \gamma  &amp; \gamma  &amp; \beta   \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$($$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) $$-$$ $$\alpha$$(0 $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) + $$\gamma$$(0 $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$$$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$$$\gamma$$ + $$\alpha$$$$\gamma$$ $$-$$ $$\gamma$$<sup>2</sup> = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\gamma$$<sup>2</sup> = $$\alpha$$$$\beta$$<br><br>Hence, $$\gamma$$ is GM of $$\alpha$$ and $$\beta$$.

