We have,<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   x &amp; y &amp; 3  \cr 
   {{x^2}} &amp; {5{y^3}} &amp; 9  \cr 
   {{x^3}} &amp; {10{y^5}} &amp; {27}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ [by C<sub>1</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>1</sub> $$-$$ C<sub>3</sub>]<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {x - 3} &amp; y &amp; 3  \cr 
   {{x^2} - 9} &amp; {5{y^3}} &amp; 9  \cr 
   {{x^3} - 27} &amp; {10{y^5}} &amp; {27}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$ <br><br>(x $$-$$ 3) common by C<sub>1</sub><br><br>$$ = (x - 3)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; y &amp; 3  \cr 
   {x + 3} &amp; {5{y^3}} &amp; 9  \cr 
   {{x^2} + 9 + 3x} &amp; {10{y^5}} &amp; {27}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>Hence, (x $$-$$ 3) is a factor of given determinant.

